<ol><li>The printer&nbsp;<b>generates a bitmap image</b>&nbsp;of the printed page.</li><li>Using a laser and a mirror,&nbsp;<b>draws a negative</b>&nbsp;onto a negatively charged drum. The laser light causes the affected areas of the drum to&nbsp;<b>lose their charge</b>.</li><li>The drum rotates pass a&nbsp;<b>toner hopper</b>&nbsp;to attract<b> charged toner particles</b>&nbsp;onto areas which have not been lasered.</li><li>The particles are&nbsp;<b>transferred to a sheet of paper</b>&nbsp;and bonded onto it using pressure and heat.</li></ol>